OL,6,F"An inquest is not a criminal trial,
OL,7,Fit is not a process for apportioning
OL,8,Fblame. It is important to remember
OL,9,Fthat the inquest is simply an attempt
OL,10,Fto establish the facts."
OL,12,FThe inquest had been told by Mark
OL,13,FJarvis, a principal inspector for the
OL,14,FAAIB, that the helicopter spun because
OL,15,Fof a mechanical fault of a bearing in
OL,16,Fthe tail rotor which became "seized"
OL,17,Fafter its lubrication broke down
OL,18,Fcausing a control shaft to rotate and
OL,19,Fbecome unscrewed.
